<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Regulation lims:pit-date="2018-12-17" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-12-17" lims:current-date="2025-07-24" lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858073" lims:id="858073" gazette-part="II" regulation-type="SOR" xml:lang="en" xmlns:lims="http://justice.gc.ca/lims"><Identification lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858074" lims:id="858074"><InstrumentNumber>SOR/2018-288</InstrumentNumber><RegistrationDate><Date><YYYY>2018</YYYY><MM>12</MM><DD>17</DD></Date></RegistrationDate><ConsolidationDate lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17"><Date><YYYY>2025</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>25</DD></Date></ConsolidationDate><EnablingAuthority lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858076" lims:id="858076"><XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="C-54.011">CUSTOMS TARIFF</XRefExternal></EnablingAuthority><LongTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858077" lims:id="858077">In-Transit Steel Goods Remission Order</LongTitle><RegulationMakerOrder><RegulationMaker>P.C.</RegulationMaker><OrderNumber>2018-1610</OrderNumber><Date><YYYY>2018</YYYY><MM>12</MM><DD>14</DD></Date></RegulationMakerOrder></Identification><Order lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858078" lims:id="858078"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858079" lims:id="858079" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Her Excellency the Governor General in Council, on the recommendation of the Minister of Finance, pursuant to section 115<FootnoteRef idref="fn_a">a</FootnoteRef> of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="C-54.011">Customs Tariff</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="fn_b">b</FootnoteRef>, makes the annexed <XRefExternal reference-type="regulation">In-Transit Steel Goods Remission Order</XRefExternal>.</Text><Footnote id="fn_a" placement="page" status="official"><Label>a</Label><Text>S.C. 2005, c. 38, par. 145(2)(j)</Text></Footnote><Footnote id="fn_b" placement="page" status="official"><Label>b</Label><Text>S.C. 1997, c. 36</Text></Footnote></Provision></Order><Body lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858080" lims:id="858080"><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858081" lims:id="858081"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858082" lims:id="858082">Remission</MarginalNote><Label>1</Label><Text>Subject to subsection (2), remission is granted of the surtax paid or payable under the <XRefExternal reference-type="regulation" link="SOR-2025-148">Order Imposing a Surtax on the Importation of Certain Steel Goods</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="fn_1">1</FootnoteRef> in respect of goods that were in transit to Canada before October 25, 2018.</Text><Footnote id="fn_1" placement="page" status="official"><Label>1</Label><Text>SOR/2018-206</Text></Footnote></Section><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858083" lims:id="858083"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858084" lims:id="858084">Conditions</MarginalNote><Label>2</Label><Text>The remission is granted if</Text><Paragraph lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858085" lims:id="858085"><Label>(a)</Label><Text>the good is imported into Canada on or after October 25, 2018; and</Text></Paragraph><Paragraph lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858086" lims:id="858086"><Label>(b)</Label><Text>a claim for remission is made to the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness within two years after the date of importation.</Text></Paragraph></Section><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858087" lims:id="858087"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2018-12-17" lims:fid="858088" lims:id="858088">Coming into force</MarginalNote><Label>3</Label><Text>This Order comes into force on the day on which it is registered.</Text></Section></Body></Regulation>